Ha-Gan starring a very young Melanie Griffith. An elderly couple, Abraham and Sarah, tend a garden which makes them a modest income. Big business comes a-calling, offering big money to buy and redevelop the land. Abraham refuses, as the garden doesn't belong to him but to God. Meanwhile, a young girl wanders through the city, seemingly lost and confused. It doesn't help, then, that she's being chased by a gang of youths who see her as easy prey for them to abuse. An altercation between the girl and the youths leads to her ending up, inevitably, naked, and en route to the garden. Worth seeing if you're interested in seeing Melanie before the tattoos, drugs, Don Johnson, etc.


